JOHANNESBURG - If you’ve seen movies like Dreamgirls and Everything Everything, or the popular TV shows Power and The Quad, then you'll recognise the many faces and talents of Anika Noni Rose. Rose is one several black female actresses who are pushing for diversity in Hollywood. She's worked on a number of notable projects, including playing the first ever Black Walt Disney Princess in the Princess and the Frog. She’s also a member of the Selection Committee for the Academy Awards. That means she's responsible for picking films that can be shortlisted for Oscar nominations. Following International Women’s Day, eNCA continues to celebrate inspirational women. Lindiwe Sithole caught up with Anika Noni Rose - you can watch the video in 2 parts below. Thandi Ntuli opens up about her musical career https://t.co/pnh10POAKB eNCA